arrays - sorted

Write a method named sorted that accepts an array of doubles as a parameter and returns true if the list is in sorted order and false if not. For example, if an array named list stores {1.5, 4.3, 7.0, 19.5, 25.1, 46.2} respectively, the call of sorted(list) should return true. You may assume the array has at least one element.
A one-element array is considered to be sorted. Do not modify the array passed in.

 public static boolean sorted (double[] doubles) { 
        for(int i = 0; i < doubles.length - 1; i++) {
            if (doubles[i] > doubles[i + 1]) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }



